title Part 0.4

note over browser:
Browser sends data contained in the form to the address
end note

browser->server:\n HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note

note over server:
Server responds with a URI redirect telling the browser to make
a new GET request to the slug "/notes", i.e. redirects the browser
end note

server-->browser:\n Status code 302: found
browser->server:\n HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
server-->browser:\n HTML
browser->server:\n HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
server-->browser:\n main.css
browser->server:\n HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
server-->browser:\n main.js

note over browser:
Browser starts executing main.js which contains a GET
request of a JSON-file (data.js) from the server
end note

browser->server:\n HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json

note over server:
Server responds with the JSON-file which contains an array
of objects with information on the content and date of each note
end note

server-->browser:\n data.json

note over browser:
When readyState is "done", the code in main.js parses the JSON in
data.json and renders the content of each note to display
end note

